[For a discussion of scrub typhus, see moderator comments in prior ProMED-mail posts below [see archive 20150821.3582448 - Mod.LM].

Sri Ganganagar, in Sri Ganganagar district, is a planned city and the northern-most city of the Indian state of Rajasthan, situated near borders of Rajasthan and Punjab states. The Jaipur Division is 1 of 7 divisions in Rajasthan State; Dausa, Jaipur, Jhunjhunu, and Sikar are districts in Jaipur Division. The city of Jaipur, which is Rajasthan's capital and largest city, is the Jaipur district's headquarters. It is the 10th most populous district out of 640 in India (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rajasthan). A map of Rajasthan's districts can be found at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_districts_of_Rajasthan#/media/File:Map_rajasthan_dist_all_shaded.png. - Mod.ML

